{
  "stem": "4695.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I came in the service, I called [INAUDIBLE], in-- this was in March, 1936.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we go, they start teaching us-- you see-- how's that-- how to fight, how to shoot, and everything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The training, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after two weeks, comes the-- the leader from our platoon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even the captain from the Polish officers was very anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the platoon leader comes to me, and told me, Ignac, I am very proud that you coming to my platoon because you're one of the best.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Once was comes as they bring us every Friday to the synagogue, Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The same thing like they bring the Catholics Sunday to the church.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's Friday evening, only they bring it to the-- but this I like to notice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When comes Passover, they bring us to the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then the city organized for the Jewish soldiers a Passover evening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When we come back to the [NON-ENGLISH], this is--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The barracks, a group of Polish soldiers-- a group of Polish soldiers start talking to teach the Jew a lesson because they wake us up in middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they start, you know that, to give our coats to throw over somebody into heat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I see they start-- they come close to other two Jewish boys.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they know me, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I, the first, jump out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I take out my bayonet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I tell them, listen-- who will only touch somebody, I swear by God, and I swear by my uniform, will be killed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And now you can do.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or you go back in your places.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Or you like to attack with bayonets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Everything was quiet.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They backed up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I-- in my-- I don't know-- where I was born-- [INAUDIBLE], or this was I-- I don't know my individual--",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
